article_id:1249,category_name:Events,title_name:New Void Enemies and Void Battle Limited-Time Endeavors![Update],image_path:https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/7d88b49dba955f1b9fa3c91a644afc4a.png,message:<div><span style="color: rgb(44, 130, 201);"><strong>[Addendum <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1588074600"></span>]</strong></span><br>We have confirmed an issue in some Void Battles between <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1588053600"></span> and <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1588073400"></span> where the &quot;Drops X2&quot; icon wasn&#39;t displaying on quest banners even though the dropped rewards were effectively doubled for these quests. We have confirmed that the amounts of dropped rewards for these quests were correct.<br><br>This issue has now been resolved.<br><br>■Affected Quests<br>Gust Shroom Strike<br>Frost Hermit Strike<br>Infernal Phantom Strike<br><br>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div><div><br></div><hr><div>New Void enemies will be added to Void Battles (event quests where you can battle powerful boss enemies) at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1587362400"></span>.</div><div><br></div><div>You can craft new weapons using the materials obtained by defeating the newly added Void enemies.</div><div><br></div><div>Furthermore, Limited Void Battle Endeavors will be available between <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1587362400"></span> and <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1588226399"></span>.</div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/7d88b49dba955f1b9fa3c91a644afc4a.png"></div><div>Fierce gales steeped in black mana rage and howl, billowing into a frenzied hurricane. They are the manifestation of a deeply malicious intent. Typhoons. Frigid mountain gusts. Whirlwinds. The biting winds of winter. The chimera inhales them all and blasts out a cyclonic roar!</div><div><br></div><div>■New Void Enemies</div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/03b34ded64e7a935b6ce7516d0e12efc.png"></div><div>Tempest Chimera (Wind), Required Might: 13,000</div><div>With its two powerful abilities, Overgrowth and Frenzy, this mighty foe grows more and more dangerous as the fight rages on! You&#39;ll also need to watch out for the burn and stun afflictions.</div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/67375d7bc779301bc4cf1450565b3654.png"></div><div>Infernal Phantom (Flame), Required Might: 12,000</div><div>This powerful foe&#39;s Soul Eater ability restores HP based on the damage dealt to adventurers! You&#39;ll also need to watch out for the enemies summoned with Spectral Shield!</div><div><br></div><div>■Crafting</div><div>Craftable Void weapons will be added.</div><div>・Weapons that can be crafted using materials obtained from the Infernal Phantom have been added.</div><div>・Weapons that can be crafted using materials obtained from the Tempest Chimera have been added.</div><div><br></div><div>■Void Battles Schedule</div><div>The following Void Battles will be available every day starting <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1588053600"></span>.</div><div>・Scalding Shroom Strike</div><div>・Gust Shroom Strike</div><div>・Wandering Shroom Strike</div><div>・Blazing Ghost Strike</div><div>・Cerulean Ghost Strike</div><div>・Lambent Ghost Strike</div><div>・Violet Ghost Strike</div><div>・Frost Hermit Strike</div><div>・Twilight Hermit Strike</div><div>・Steel Golem Strike</div><div>・Amber Golem Strike</div><div>・Obsidian Golem Strike</div><div>・Catoblepas Fotia Strike</div><div>・Catoblepas Anemos Strike</div><div>・Infernal Phantom Strike</div><div>・Eolian Phantom Strike</div><div>・Smoldering Manticore Strike</div><div>・Greedy Manticore Strike</div><div>・Proud Manticore Strike</div><div>・Raging Manticore Strike</div><div><br></div><div>You can play Void Battles anytime, regardless of the day of the week. However, the Void enemies that appear will differ based on the day. Check out the Void Battles Schedule notification for information about when each Void enemy is scheduled to appear.</div><div><a href="https://dragalialost.com/en/news/detail/19999">Void Battles Schedule</a></div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: rgb(44, 130, 201);"><strong>[Addendum <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1587952200"></span>]</strong></span><br>The quest clear record and quest endeavor completion status for Void Battles that appear each day will be reset at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1588053600"></span>.<br>Note: The completion status for Normal and Limited endeavors under Endeavors will not reset.</div><div><br></div><div>■Using Skip Tickets</div><div>Starting <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1588053600"></span> it will be possible to use skip tickets in the following Void Battles.</div><div><br></div><div>・Scalding Shroom Strike</div><div>・Gust Shroom Strike</div><div>・Wandering Shroom Strike</div><div>・Blazing Ghost Strike</div><div>・Cerulean Ghost Strike</div><div>・Lambent Ghost Strike</div><div>・Violet Ghost Strike</div><div>・Frost Hermit Strike</div><div>・Twilight Hermit Strike</div><div>・Steel Golem Strike</div><div>・Amber Golem Strike</div><div>・Obsidian Golem Strike</div><div>・Catoblepas Fotia Strike</div><div>・Catoblepas Anemos Strike</div><div>・Infernal Phantom Strike</div><div>・Eolian Phantom Strike</div><div>・Smoldering Manticore Strike</div><div>・Greedy Manticore Strike</div><div>・Proud Manticore Strike</div><div>・Raging Manticore Strike</div><div><br></div><div>With the addition of the ability to use skip tickets, the survival bonus reward will be removed from the following Void Battles.</div><div><br></div><div>・Smoldering Manticore Strike</div><div>・Greedy Manticore Strike</div><div>・Proud Manticore Strike</div><div>・Raging Manticore Strike</div><div><br></div><div>The rewards you could previously acquire as a survival bonus prior to the change will be added to the drop rewards instead.</div><div><br></div><div>■Limited-Time Endeavors</div><div>We&#39;re adding Limited-Time Void Battle Endeavors, separated into Daily and Limited variations.</div><div>You can complete the endeavors to obtain various rewards.</div><div><br></div><div>■Limited Void Battle Endeavors Duration</div><div><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1587362400"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1588226399"></span></div><div><br></div><div>■Other</div><div>・The ability for weapons crafted using materials obtained from the lambent ghost has been changed to Petrify &amp; Soul Eater Res.</div><div><br></div><div>Notes:</div><div>1. For more information about Void Battles, tap Quests on the Home page, then go to the Void Battles page and select Help.</div><div>2. For more information about Void enemies, tap Quests on the Home page, then go to the Void Battles page and check Details on the various quest pages.</div><div>3. You can check the Endeavors added for a limited time by tapping Endeavors on the Home page, then selecting the Daily or Limited tabs.</div><div>4. Players must have completed up to Chapter 7 / 5-6 (Normal) of the main campaign in order to participate in Void Battles.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div><div><br></div>,start_time:1587362400,update_time1588075529